President Muhammadu Buhari, on Wednesday, hosted the Governor of Kaduna State, Mallam Nasir El-Rufai. The meeting took place at the State House in Abuja. This was confirmed by Buhari’s Personal Assistant on New Media, Bashir Ahmaad, via his Twitter handle. Ahmaad wrote: “President @MBuhari receives the Kaduna State Governor, Mallam Nasir @elrufai this evening at the State House, Abuja.” The meeting comes hours after Buhari presided over the fourth weekly virtual Federal Executive Council (FEC) meeting. About 10 Ministers were physically present for the FEC meeting, as the partial lockdown at the Presidential Villa, has been relaxed. Others joined by video conference.